Interface Streamable<T>

    public interface Streamable<T>
    Interface for objects that can produce a Stream on demand. This interface only requires implementation of a stream() method so it can easily be used with lambdas.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods Default Methods

      default java.util.stream.Stream<T> parallelStream()
      Produce a Stream for use in parallel computations if possible.
      java.util.stream.Stream<T> stream()
      Produce a Stream supporting non-parallel computations.

default java.util.stream.Stream<T> parallelStream()
        Produce a Stream for use in parallel computations if possible. Might return a non-parallel stream if the underlying class does not support splitting the stream.
